==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Areca
<hw>A*re"ca</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Canarese
<ets>adiki</ets>: cf. Pg. & Sp. <ets>areca</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of palms, one species of which
(<spn>Areca catechu</spn>) produces the areca nut, or betel nut, which
is chewed in India and Southeast Asia with the leaf of the <spn>Piper
Betle</spn> and lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

